“23.In making the order I take into account the following matters. Firstly, the order for costs must be proportionate with the amount at stake and the complexity of the issues. Proportionality is to be judged by a two-fold test namely, initially, whether the global sum is proportionate to the amount at stake. Next, if the global sum is disproportionate the court should look at the component parts in order to determine if they are proportionate (see Lownds v Home Office 
		[2002] EWCA Civ 365
	      ).
